<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Toad" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Toad,</orth> a paddock, Bufo; emblem of loathsomeness: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.340" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 340</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.268" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 81</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.170" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 181</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.181" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 181</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.61" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 90</bibl>. Thought to be venomous: <bibl n="shak. luc 850" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 850</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.246" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 246</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 6</bibl>. Having a precious stone in its head: <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 13</bibl>. Changing eyes with the lark: <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 31</bibl>.
